      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Find the value of $c$ such that $2x^2 - 4x + c = 0$ has no real solutions.",
        "options": ["$c > 2$", "$c < 2$", "$c \\ge 2$", "$c \\le 2$"],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "For no real solutions, $b^2 - 4ac < 0$. $16 - 8c < 0 \\implies 16 < 8c \\implies c > 2$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Solve the equation $|x + 4| = |x - 2|$.",
        "options": ["$x = -1$", "$x = 1$", "$x = 0$", "No solution"],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "Case 1: $x+4 = x-2$ (no solution). Case 2: $x+4 = -(x-2) \\implies x+4 = -x+2 \\implies 2x = -2 \\implies x = -1$."
      },
